    "description": "Amazing graphics. Countless different units. An addictive Battle Pass. We have none of those things, but we are very, very cheap!<br><br>Take command of a lone Carrier as you attempt to cross the solar system in a retro arcade swarm shooter set among the planets and moons of our own corner of space. With a minimalist design aesthetic like it was a refugee from the 90s, Scramble All Fighters! takes seconds to learn, but will only yield ultimate victory to someone willing to master its deceptively simple tactical, strategic, and logistical challenges.<br><br>Victory is not enough... you may win the battle, but still lose the war!<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li>Tiny fighters, big battles! It's flocking brilliant<br></li><li>Minimalist game design and effortless two-button controls<br></li><li>Challenging sectors where victory requires winning up to nine consecutive battles<br></li><li>Rewind time when a key battle goes wrong - spend your Timewarps with care!<br></li><li>Kids mode for anyone looking for a less demanding campaign</li></ul>",
